#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:1
msgid "Feature Name: rust-lang_github_org_access_policy"
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:2
msgid "Start Date: 2020-03-02"
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:4
msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:7
msgid ""
"This RFC proposes a policy for managing permissions to the [Rust-Lang GitHub "
"Organization](https://www.github.com/rust-lang) and repositories within this "
"organization."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:9
msgid ""
"This RFC was written in consultation with the Governance Working Group and "
"the Infrastructure team. Most discussion took place on [this issue](https://"
"github.com/rust-lang/wg-governance/issues/4) and [this pull request](https://"
"github.com/rust-lang/wg-governance/pull/42)."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:11
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:14
msgid ""
"Access control for the [Rust-Lang GitHub Organization](https://www.github."
"com/rust-lang) and repositories within that organization is currently "
"managed either through the [rust-lang team database](https://github.com/rust-"
"lang/team/), or ad-hoc via the GitHub UI by the org owners. We need a policy "
"that defines how these accesses are granted and managed. This will allow us "
"to have greater security in permissions to our GitHub org, and provide "
"transparency and clarity on how access is managed."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:18
msgid "Guide-level explanation"
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:21
msgid "Rust-Lang GitHub Permissions Policy"
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:23
msgid ""
"This policy applies to both the [Rust-Lang GitHub Organization](https://"
"github.com/rust-lang/) and all repositories within that organization."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:25
msgid "Rust-Lang Organization"
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:27
msgid ""
"Access to the Rust-Lang GitHub organization is managed with the [rust-lang "
"team database](https://github.com/rust-lang/team/). The team database is "
"managed by the [team-repo-admins](https://github.com/rust-lang/team/blob/"
"master/teams/team-repo-admins.toml), whose policies are specified in the "
"[Team Maintenance](https://forge.rust-lang.org/infra/team-maintenance.html) "
"documentation."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:29
msgid ""
"Selected members of the [Infrastructure Team](https://github.com/rust-lang/"
"team/blob/master/teams/infra.toml) can also be organization owners if their "
"work requires it."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:31
msgid ""
"All GitHub accounts used to interact with the Rust-Lang GitHub organization "
"(owner or non-owner) must have 2FA enabled."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:37
msgid "Rust-Lang Repositories"
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:39
msgid ""
"Access to and permissions for repositories within the Rust-Lang organization "
"must be administered through the [rust-lang team database](https://github."
"com/rust-lang/team/). Permissions should not be given to individuals, only "
"to teams or groups."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:41
msgid ""
"GitHub provides several permission levels for access to a repository. Please "
"refer to [GitHub's documentation](https://help.github.com/en/github/setting-"
"up-and-managing-organizations-and-teams/repository-permission-levels-for-an-"
"organization) for details on permission levels and what each level can do."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:43
msgid ""
"Repositories in the Rust-Lang organization should follow these permission "
"guidelines:"
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:45
msgid ""
"**Admin** --- No users or teams except for org owners should have this "
"permission level."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:46
msgid ""
"**Maintain** --- Teams may have this permission level at their discretion "
"for repositories the team is responsible for. Repositories using the [bors]"
"(https://github.com/rust-lang/homu) bot may want to consider using the "
"_write_ permission level instead in order to deactivate the \"Merge\" button "
"on PRs to enforce that merges go through bors."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:48
msgid ""
"**Write** --- Teams that are responsible for a repository should have at "
"least this permission level."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:49
msgid ""
"**Triage** --- This role is available if teams want to give these "
"permissions to other teams, such as for triage support. Unfortunately this "
"role does not allow contributors to edit issue descriptions or titles, so "
"its utility for that purpose is limited."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:50
msgid ""
"**Read** --- This role is unnecessary, and should not be used (it is "
"generally only relevant to private repositories, and we do not have a use "
"case for it)."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:52
msgid ""
"Teams who are responsible for a repository may give access to other teams at "
"their discretion."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:54
msgid ""
"Teams or groups may ask for repositories to be created to fulfill their "
"needs by opening a PR to the [Team Repository](https://github.com/rust-lang/"
"team/). It is up to the team-repo-admins to approve creating the "
"repositories. Existing repositories that need to be transferred from outside "
"the rust-lang organization should consult with the Infrastructure Team to "
"fulfill that request."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:56
msgid ""
"By default, repositories should be public and allow read access to all. When "
"needed, some repositories can have limited read access (i.e. repositories "
"related to security)."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:58
msgid ""
"Some teams - such as the moderation team - need broad access to public Rust-"
"Lang repositories. The first way to manage this is through creating a GitHub "
"team managed through the [Team Repository](https://github.com/rust-lang/"
"team/) and granting that team appropriate permissions to the appropriate "
"repos. Another way is to create tooling that will allow a member of the "
"moderation team to selectively and temporarily gain the access that they "
"need when it is needed (such as deleting a comment or issue). For now, we "
"are proceeding with managing access to repos for moderation through a GitHub "
"team, however, should it be needed, we can develop tooling to apply more "
"fine grained and time limited access."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:60
msgid ""
"Bot accounts controlled by the Infrastructure Team (such as the [triagebot]"
"(https://forge.rust-lang.org/triagebot/index.html)) can be granted any level "
"of access required for them to work at the discretion of the Infrastructure "
"Team."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:65
msgid "Implementation"
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:67
msgid ""
"It is the responsibility of the Leadership Council, the Infrastructure Team, "
"and the team-repo-admins to finish the migration to implement this policy. "
"New teams may need to be created, which is outside the scope of this RFC to "
"define."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:69
msgid "Drawbacks"
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:72
msgid ""
"There can be exceptional cases where a team wants to give repository access "
"to an individual to assist with their work. Requiring them to join or create "
"a team in order to perform that work can be a significant hassle. Teams who "
"find they need this frequently should consider creating a \"contributors\" "
"subteam for that purpose, or to investigate other tooling to assist with "
"what they need."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:74
msgid "Unresolved questions"
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:77
msgid ""
"Should these rules applied to Rust-Lang affiliated repositories and "
"organizations that are outside of the [Rust-Lang GitHub Org](https://www."
"github.com/rust-lang), such as [rust-embedded](https://github.com/rust-"
"embedded)?"
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:79
msgid "Future possibilities"
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:81
msgid ""
"[Custom GitHub Roles](https://docs.github.com/en/enterprise-cloud@latest/"
"organizations/managing-user-access-to-your-organizations-repositories/"
"managing-repository-roles/about-custom-repository-roles) could be created "
"for use cases where the existing roles do not suffice."
msgstr ""

#: src/2872-github-access-policy.md:82
msgid ""
"Extend tooling, such as [triagebot](https://forge.rust-lang.org/triagebot/"
"index.html), to provide extended permissions that are not normally available "
"(for example, it currently offers [labeling](https://forge.rust-lang.org/"
"triagebot/labeling.html))."
msgstr ""
